.SH INLINE ASSEMBLY
Zen C supports GCC-style inline assembly with simplified syntax:
.PP
.nf
fn atomic_add(a: int, b: int) -> int {
    var result: int;
    asm {
        "add {result}, {a}, {b}"
        : out(result)
        : in(a), in(b)
        : clobber("cc")
    }
    return result;
}
.fi
